    "abstract": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>We attempted to explain the rare mutation at the receptor binding domain of the spike protein in the XAY.2 variant of SARS-CoV-2 from the perspective of hydrophobic interactions. We propose that decreasing hydrophobicity at position 446 and 486 of the RBD region of the spike protein might affect the infectivity of SARS-CoV-2. We also estimated the probable mutations at the 446 and 486 position the virus may acquire, leading to a decreased hydrophobicity.</jats:p>",
